.SH NAME
device_change_owner \- change the owner of an existing device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" device_change_owner
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "kuid_t kuid "  ","
.BI "kgid_t kgid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device.
.IP "kuid" 12
new owner's kuid
.IP "kgid" 12
new owner's kgid
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This changes the owner of \fIdev\fP and its corresponding sysfs entries to
\fIkuid\fP/\fIkgid\fP. This function closely mirrors how \fIdev\fP was added via driver
core.

Returns 0 on success or error code on failure.
